                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="a1">
                    <locus target="#141v" facs="142"> f. 141, column 1</locus>
                    <desc>
                    Prayers for blessing, mentioning, <foreign xml:lang="gez">ኃጥእ፡ ገብርኪ፡ ዮሴፍ፡</foreign>, <q>“your sinful servant, Yosef,”</q> perhaps the scribe
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="a7">
                    <locus target="#141v" facs="142"> f. 141v, column 2</locus>
                    <desc type="OwnershipNote">
                    later note of ownership, written in another purple ink
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="a8">
                    <locus target="#144v" facs="145"> f. 144v and passim</locus>
                    <desc>
                    mentioning Akala Qal, <foreign xml:lang="gez">አካለ፡ ቃል፡</foreign>, in various places in the original hand, often with the name, <foreign xml:lang="gez">ገብረ ኢየሱስ</foreign>, Gabra Iyasus written above, in a slightly different shade of red ink
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="a">
                    <locus target="#149r" facs="149"> f. 149r, column 2, bottom</locus>
                    <desc type="OwnershipNote">
                    added note of ownership by, <foreign xml:lang="gez">ገብረ ኢየሱስ</foreign>, Gabra Iyasus
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                  </list>
